  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. Since each term in the given expression has a common factor of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x squared\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, it can be rewritten as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 13 minus 7 right parenthesis x squared\"><mo>(</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>)</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6 x squared\"><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>. Therefore, the expression <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6 x squared\"><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> is equivalent to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"13 x squared minus 7 x squared\"><mn>13</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Alternate approach: Since the two terms of the given expression are both constant multiples of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x squared\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, they are like terms and can, therefore, be combined through subtraction. Subtracting like terms in the expression <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"13 x squared minus 7 x squared\"><mn>13</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6 x squared\"><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice A is incorrect. This expression is equivalent to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 13 x right parenthesis left parenthesis minus 7 x right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mn>13</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>, not&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"13 x squared minus 7 x squared\"><mn>13</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice C is incorrect. This expression is equivalent to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"13 x squared plus 7 x squared\"><mn>13</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"13 x squared minus 7 x squared\"><mn>13</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>",
